 were gone.  They wander off somehow or BoF expires while I'm gaining that distance on the unsnared fourth.  TBoots are slower than most SoWs.<br><br>The typical situation is I snare three and one resists, I run ahead with the one that resisted so I can get distance for another cast (root, stun, another snare, etc.) and I've lost the original three.<br><br>At this point, I'm thinking I'll just run under the Cliff Golem's legs and let him take out the non-cooperative MoB and then go back for the others.<br><br>What is the best way to handle a situation where they all don't get snared?<br><br>Also, I accidentally re-cast BoF on an already snared group of two last night.  The results indicated the spell took hold.  Does this reset the timer on the BoF spell?  Can I resnare and give myself a longer time?<br><br>I got a great screen shot of the whole file of Dragoons attacking and killng two unsnared MoBs I brought to them while the Dragoons were on-the-march out.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=stiffu>Stiffu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/01 3:40:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hope this helps.</span><hr size=1> Quad kiting is surprisingly simple, the key to being a successful Quad Kiter is the mobs you are quading.  I'll attempt to answer some of your questions in the following. ;-)<br><br>&quot;Typically because at least one MoB resists my BoF...What is the best way to handle a situation where they all don't get snared?&quot;<br>In most Kunark zones if you run too far away from a mob then they'll stop chasing you but still remember you.  The best way to round up mobs for a quad kite is to aggro them all (with TFlux) run in a circle to bunch them all up, then run away (using Tflux to gauge distance, until you get a few out of range messages)  then stop for a second, and spam bonds of force, Dont worry even mobs with SoW won't get close enough to you during the casting time to make you snare yourself also, just make sure you are &quot;out of range&quot; before casting BoF.<br><br>If you get partial resists it's ok, just take off again (I recommend circling around and running back the way you came so your snared mobs are relatively close)  Wait until out of range, and snare the mobs that resisted.  If you did this correctly you should be about to circle back around and pick up your previously snared mobs.  Get them bunched back together (you have time for 2 or 3 CoF's depending on how long you take to get them rebunched before you have to refresh BoF. . .)<br><br>&quot;Can I resnare and give myself a longer time?&quot;<br><br>Yes.  I find that if I refresh BoF after about 8 CoF's i have ample time to get them all resnared before original snare breaks.<br><br>Also, in closing, I suggest you head to Eastern wastes instead of OT to start quading.  (if you zone in from IC just follow the shore to the left until you hit a wall, you'll be in . . . SouthWest corner if im not mistaken, in this area you'll find tons of walruses, you can quad these up and down the shoreline until 38ish when you should do Ulthork Hunters and Warriors and Coldain camps (if you want to be ally in Kael)  Save all Ulthork Tusks and Coldain Heads as they are used for good quests. you can get to 43 (maybe 44 don't remember) easily.<br><br>Hope it helped ;-) good luck<br><br>Stiffu Noob<br>Luclin - currently 49 wizard<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspankda.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spankda</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/01 4:06:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> EW MoB Speed</span><hr size=1> Are the Walruses, Ulthork's, and Coldains all pretty slow?<br><br>I've found Tigers and Rhino's in OT to be too fast for me to kite even in singles.<br><br>I'm gonna stay in OT until I get that stupid hammer with an amiable faction.  It takes 40 whips to go up one faction level (apprehensive to indifferent). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chiriko>chiriko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/01 2:22:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New At Quad Kiting -- 35 Wizard's Questions</span><hr size=1> yes, walruses, ulthraks, and coldain are all pretty slow, though I'd stay away from the coldain if I were you unless you want to join the giant faction. I highly recommend you try the drakkel wolves in greater Divide, they're pretty slow, all over the place, and have low resists to magic.<br><br>As a side note, I have to say that quad kiting in GD is some of the most fun I've had with my wizard, every pull is different. sure, occasionally everything goes perfectly, snare sticks on all four,and I'm done with 40m, but more often than not 1 will resist, or something will go wrong.. and then the *Real* fun begins. there's nothing quite like having 2 dogs after you, snare about to break, and half a bubble left... 'cause then you have to make the tough calls.. re snare them and kite&amp;med until you can CoF them again? run ahead and cast harvest, hope that snare doesn't break while you're stunned? nuke one so that the other one starts to run and you have time to med to finish him off? And then what if one of *those* tactics fail, like you try to resnare, and one resists? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I can't tell ya how many times over the past 4 levels I've stood over 4 dead wolves utterly out of mana but vicorious, having been sure just seconds ago that I would never be able to pull it off.<br><br>To date, I've died exactly *once* quad kiting, and that was because lightning hit a powerpole down the street and knocked power out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>-Chiriko, lvl 39 wizard, Innoruuk<br>.... all flush with wizzy power. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showPrevMessage?topicID=66.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showNextMessage?topicID=66.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=66.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.emailToFriend?topicID=66.topic><im